title: From Duke Ellington to Blues Alley: What’s With D.C.’s Jazz Scene These Days?
description:
"Are there still jazz clubs where up-and-coming artists perform?" Sasha-Ann Simons joins Mikaela to answer a question from a recent transplant to Damascus, MD. And we learn what role one embassy played in D.C.'s jazz history.

To submit a question, visit wamu.org/whatswith.

The What’s With Washington podcast is made possible by our listeners. To support the show, visit wamu.org/donate/.
